philipm.cs5.software.development.server.system

Class Queue

  • java.lang.Object
    • philipm.cs5.software.development.server.system.Queue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class Queue
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    Creates a new Queue which handle the server's requests to write to files and change arrays. Essentially, this object allows threads from an unknown number of client's to interact with a server sequentially. All processing is performed on one thread to avoid issues that may arise from two threads writing simultaneously to the same file. This is justified as the user base is very small.
    Author:
    mortimer

        private void deleteGame(int GAME_ID,
                        double RESULT)

        Parameters:
        GAME_ID - the game id to delete
        RESULT - The game result. 1 indicates that player one won, 0.5 indicates a draw and 0 indicates that player two won
